DSA-008
1. 1D Arrays (Single Dimension) 📏
🧠 Logic:
Array ek fixed-size ka container hai jo ek hi data type ke elements ko store karta hai. Indexing hamesha 0 se shuru hoti hai.

📌 Example:

Java

// Declaration, initialization, and access
int[] arr = new int[3];
arr[0] = 10;
arr[1] = 20;

System.out.println(arr[0]); // 10
System.out.println(arr.length); // 3
🔤 Java Code:
Java

public class ArrayExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Initialization
        int[] numbers = {10, 20, 30, 40};

        // Traversing (Elements ko print karna)
        for (int i = 0; i < numbers.length; i++) {
            System.out.print(numbers[i] + " ");
        }
        
        System.out.println(); // Newline

        // Enhanced For Loop (For-Each)
        for (int num : numbers) {
            System.out.print(num + " ");
        }
    }
}

// Output:
// 10 20 30 40 
// 10 20 30 40 
🧾 Notebook Points:
Java

📘 1D Array:
→ Fixed size container
→ Same data type elements
→ Index starts from 0

🔢 Access: arr[i]
